dict.string: This is a demonstration of the toolkit with two virtual humans, myself and Rachel.
Hello, I'm Rachel, a virtual human.
Brad, why don't you go ahead and tell them about the toolkit?
I like my name a lot.
Because my animations are procedurally and dynamically scheduled to match my voice, my gestures might be less fluent than expected. This issue is currently looked into.

The utterances you speak are sent to the N P C Editor, a statistical text classifier, which selects my best response. The non verbal behavior generator then specifies my gestures and gaze, which are synchronized with my voice by SmartBody.
If Smith sounds boring, then it matches my voice perfectly.
I am thirty one years old.
I thought I told you already.
I am a virtual character showing off what the virtual human tool kit can do.
It's my job to show what you can do with the tool kit.
Depending on the default voice you have selected in Windows, I can sound pretty bad.
Currently I can not see you, but with the Watson module I will. Watson is a visual recognition system that will allow me to recognize head movements like gazes and nodding.
SAPI is a speech and text to speech interface by Microsoft. I use it to be able to talk to you.
I am great. How are you?
Nothing much. What's up with you?
I am just a basic example and don't have that many different lines, but you can add more in the N P C Editor if you want too.
The things I have been programmed to say are somewhat limited, but you can expand my verbal behavior.
I can answer your general questions about the tool kit. For more information, go to v h tool kit dot eye c t dot u s c dot e d u.
If the system cannot find my regular voice, it defaults back to the Windows standard voice. Depending on your version of Windows that can be a woman's voice. Don't I sound delightful?
Academic researchers and the government can use the tool kit free of charge, as long as they honor the license agreement. Currently, there is no commercial license.
You know what, I'm not exactly sure what mathematical models underlie the N P C Editor. But I'm sure you don't know either how your brain works.

My main purpose is to answer all your high level questions about the tool kit, but in the future I hope I will be able to do more, like actually seeing and reacting to you. Go online for more information.
A virtual human is a character like me. I can perceive real humans and respond both verbally and non verbally.
Our proud representative of the armed forces.

We at eye C T perform basic research as well as develop applied projects. You might have heard about sasso, Sergeant Star, Elect BiLat, Virtual Patient, our P T S D work, or Full Spectrum Warrior. We also have museum guides, intelligent tutors, and many mixed reality projects. In addition, our Graphics Lab has worked on a variety of movies, ranging from Spiderman to Avatar.
It can be quite lonely, being the only virtual human here. Maybe one day, the great people at eye C T can find it in their hearts to develop a friend for me.

The tool kit consists of many modules, tools and libraries. The main modules are the N P C Editor, which is my brain so to speak, the Non verbal Behavior Generator, which, as you've already guessed, generates my non verbal behavior, SmartBody, a procedural animation system, and Watson, a vision system.
It is nice to meet you too.
I would like to know that too.
It is nice to see you too.
The tool kit allows people like you to create their own virtual humans. It is developed at the Institute for Creative Technologies.
The Virtual Human Tool kit is a collection of modules and tools that enable humans like you to create humans like me.
With the tool kit you can create your own virtual humans. Go online to v h tool kit dot eye c t dot u s c dot e d u for more information.
You can ask me questions about myself or the virtual human tool kit.
The tool kit website is v h tool kit dot eye c t dot u s c dot e d u.
You can find us online at v h tool kit dot eye c t dot u s c dot e d u.
I know I look pretty basic, but given enough time and resources there are few limits to how a tool kit character can look.
My appearance is quite basic, but I am mostly an example of what you can do with natural language and non verbal behavior.
Well, have you ever heard yourself talk?
By default I am using a very basic text to speech engine, but you can change my voice or even the engine.
I am being developed at the Institute for Creative Technologies with the very tool kit you are using.
I did not go to school as such, but if I did, U S C would be the school for me.
The tool kit can be a great asset in creating virtual humans.
I am from the Institute for Creative Technologies.
At the eye C T, or Institute for Creative Technologies, research, hollywood storytelling, and game design come together to create innovative technologies that support new ways of learning.
eye C T stands for the Institute for Creative Technologies. It is a place where groundbreaking research is performed in areas like virtual humans, mixed reality and training.
I'm not much of a weather man.
The weather in here is always nice.
I am here to inform you about the eye C T Virtual Human Tool kit.
There is more information about the tool kit at v h tool kit dot eye c t dot u s c dot e d u.
I am alone here, but at the eye C T, there are many like me. Like Sergeant Star, Justina, Raed, Utah, Harmony, Cabrillo, and many many more.
The eye C T has created a wide variety of virtual humans. You can read about some of them at v h tool kit dot eye c t dot u s c dot e d u.
Existing animations can be used on a variety of characters, but some don't exactly fit and need tweaking.
I once heard my animations were not created for my body and need some tweaking. Probably just a rumor.

My dancing is quite embarrassing. Let's not do that.

Collaboration and competition are both good for the field. But of course we all know who's the best.
The University of Southern California, or U S C, is a leading research university. You can learn more at u s c dot e d u.

My voice uses Microsoft SAPI. You can install your own voice for me to use.
I am visualized here using the Unity or Ogre rendering engines, but SmartBody has been integrated with Gamebryo, Unreal Tournament 2004, and Panda 3 d as well.
Watson can recognize your head movements with just a basic web cam. Unfortunately, it is not integrated with me yet. You will have to launch the separate Watson demo.
With a web cam, Watson can recognize your head movements, like eye gaze, head gaze, and head gestures like nodding.
By default I am rendered in Unity, but you can also see me in the Ogre rendering engine.
Ogre is an open source rendering engine.
The N P C Editor is basically my brain. It listens to what you say and selects my response.
The N P C Editor is a statistical text classifier, matching my output to your input.
SmartBody is a procedural animation system. It enables me to pull off my beautiful moves.
All my animations are scheduled by SmartBody and timed to my voice, based on what the non verbal behavior generator has produced.
I do move my arms from time to time

The non verbal behavior generator analyzes the line I am saying and procedurally generates what gestures and body language I should use. That way, I can have different gestures even when I say the exact same thing.
The nonverbal generator, or n v b g, looks at the text I'm speaking, and generates the appropiate body language, like gaze and gestures.

Hi. Welcome to the Virtual Human Toolkit. I'm Brad and yes, I'm a virtual human. Now, you might wonder what that means exactly. Well, it means that while I may look, sound, and even act like a real person, I'm not. I was created by some brilliant people at eye C T.

But enough about them, I'm here to talk about me and the toolkit. Behind these good looks is a computer program that allows for me to hear your voice and understand what you say. Or, at least I try to understand what you say. They're still working on that, so I don't always get it right. But, when I think I understand, I respond to you. And like a real human, I respond with words and gestures.

I do my best to keep up my end of the conversation, but I'm not perfect. In fact, I'm fairly limited in what I know, so please be patient with me. You can even help out by adding to my knowledge base if I don't know the answer to your question. Remember, you can always check out the toolkit website, vhtoolkit dot ict dot usc dot edu, for more information.
So let's get started. Ask me a question. See what I have to say.
